> I think this PR already supports this, as a fetcher entry in the configuration for axios

> Interesting, would you have an example for this ?

Sure thing. [Here's how you pass configuration](https://github.com/sgammon/axios-fetch/tree/feat/fetch-adapter/examples/fetch#passing-options-to-the-fetch-adapter), and one of the config properties is `fetcher`, which [overrides the default `fetch` function used](https://github.com/sgammon/axios-fetch/blob/9b315e13f55a33ba52f02b7a206db582056d8a65/lib/adapters/fetch.js#L383).

This mechanism is used [in the tests](https://github.com/sgammon/axios-fetch/blob/feat/fetch-adapter/test/fetch/fetch_helpers.js#L232) so that `fetch` can be tested without actually fetching anything. So it should work well.

One gotcha: make sure `fetcher` is at the same level as `fetchOptions`, i.e. `fetcher` is a top-level config property:
```js
axios('https://...', {
  adapter: 'fetch',
  fetcher: someOtherFetchFunction,
  fetchOptions: {
    // fetch-specific options here
    credentials: 'include',
    mode: 'cors',
  },
});
```

If you have any trouble with it, please let me know and I'll act quickly to fix. The above should work in Deno, browsers, Cloudflare Workers, modern Node, or any other [WICG-compatible runtime](https://wintercg.org/).

(Don't let the rebase conflicts scare you -- those are normal and shouldn't cause any errors in the fetch library.)

