@gracefullight I don't know why this PR cannot pass the CI test, but there is an alternative option you can choose, during development, I've found that *dns-lookup-cache* also has some problem, so I created a new package [better-lookup](https://github.com/hyurl/better-lookup), which exposes an `install()` function that can allow you patching the custom lookup function into an HTTP(s) agent instance.

```js
const Axios = require("axios").default;
const http = require("http");
const https = require("https");
const { install } = require("better-lookup");

install(http.globalAgent); // you may want to create a custom agent via `new http.Agent()` instead
install(https.globalAgent);

(async () => {
     var res = await Axios.get("http://example.com");
})();
```

This strategy is now used in another project of mime, [@hyurl/fetch](https://github.com/hyurl/fetch), which includes a third-party proxy support for Axios, and I used better-lookup for the proxy agent as well.

