Hi again!

I've been thinking about how to solve the problem of sharing global variables in environments that you don't control.

Finally figured it out how to solve it without adding any line into axios.

I usually bundle my apps or libraries using webpack or rollup, respectivelly.

Both bundlers has ~methods~ plugins to replace global variables within the resulting code.

For example, for using [promise-polyfill](https://www.npmjs.com/package/promise-polyfill) as the default Promise:

> webpack.config.js
``` js
const webpack = require('webpack')

module.exports = {
  ...,
  plugins: [
    new webpack.ProvidePlugin({
        'Promise': 'promise-polyfill/lib/index.js',
      }),
  ],
}
```

> rollup.config.js
``` js
import inject from '@rollup/plugin-inject';

export default {
  ...,
  plugins: [
    inject({
      Promise: ['promise-polyfill'],
    })
  ],
};
```
In conclusion, thanks a lot for your feedback!!

This discussion has being very helpfull for me and allowed to get a much better solution than the proposed in the PR.

