As of today (Axios 1.6.8) and depending on your TS Config, the following worked for us (using typescript 5.2.2)

It will change the `AxiosRequestConfig` for all instances but better than nothing if you document your changes correctly.

In `global-axios.d.ts` file
```ts
export * from 'axios';

declare module 'axios' {
  interface AxiosRequestConfig {
    myField: string;
  }
}
```

Without `export * from 'axios';` tsc was not able to resolve the original types exported by axios.
Same when placing the changes in `axios.d.ts` or our `index.d.ts` / `vendors.d.ts` files.

