When an object is passed as `paramsSerializer`, it must be passed as options to `encodeParams`.

And we should add the option `arrayFormat: 'repeat'` (to fix https://github.com/axios/axios/issues/1443 like qs)

```js
axios.get(
  "/url",
  { params: { a: ["b", "c"] } },
  { paramsSerializer: { arrayFormat: "indices" } }
);
// '/url?a[0]=b&a[1]=c'

axios.get(
  "/url",
  { params: { a: ["b", "c"] } },
  { paramsSerializer: { arrayFormat: "brackets" } }
);
// '/url?a[]=b&a[]=c'

axios.get(
  "/url",
  { params: { a: ["b", "c"] } },
  { paramsSerializer: { arrayFormat: "repeat" } }
);
// '/url?a=b&a=c'
```

