Copying only headers by value (whitelisting) will not completely solve the problem. If tomorrow we have another nested default value, it will be copied by reference and can then overwrite all defaults.

A better solution is to copy all defaults by value before merging. This way, every axios instance has a copy of the defaults object that can be mutated and will only affect that instance.

