@yanivefraim What if we make `axios.defaults` a reference to the global defaults object (exported by `lib/defaults.js`) instead of creating a new object? Custom instances already use the global defaults when sending a request, so everything will work as designed.

``` js
// change the global defaults before creating an instance
axios.defaults.timeout = 100;

const instance = axios.create();
instance.get('/foo'); // timeout is 100

// change the global defaults after creating the instance
axios.defaults.timeout = 200;
instance.get('/foo'); // timeout is 200 because the global defaults are merged in request()

// also, we can override anything at the instance level
instance.defaults = 300;
instance.get('/foo'); // timeout is 300 because the instance defaults take precedence over the global defaults
```

